{%- comment -%}
  Stockly — Wholesale FPQ Banner (cart-page)

  Renders a thin banner on the merchant's cart template telling
  approved_pre_fpq customers how close they are to meeting the
  First-Purchase Qualifier (ADR-004). Mirrors the banner that
  already lives inside the Quick Order Form block, but for the
  customer's actual cart screen — so they don't lose context when
  they leave the wholesale-order page.

  Hidden when:
  - Customer is qualified (already cleared the gate)
  - Customer is a visitor (not eligible at all)
  - Shop has fpqMode = "none" (no gate configured)
  - Cart already meets the FPQ on the wholesale-price basis

  The block reads the customer's cart subtotal/qty from
  /cart.js (Shopify's storefront cart API) and computes what
  the wholesale spend WOULD be if the discount applied, then
  compares against the FPQ amount/quantity rules from the App
  Proxy /apps/stockly/context response.

  Drag this block into the cart template's "section" area in
  the theme editor. No settings — it self-configures from the
  shop's pricing config.
{%- endcomment -%}

<stockly-fpq-banner
  class="stockly-fpq"
  data-context-url="/apps/stockly/context"
  data-customer-id="{% if customer %}{{ customer.id }}{% endif %}"
  data-customer-tags="{% if customer %}{{ customer.tags | join: ',' | escape }}{% endif %}"
  {{ block.shopify_attributes }}
>
  <div class="stockly-fpq__banner" data-stockly-fpq-cart-banner hidden>
    <span class="stockly-fpq__icon" aria-hidden="true">★</span>
    <span data-stockly-fpq-cart-banner-text></span>
  </div>
</stockly-fpq-banner>

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Wholesale FPQ Banner",
  "target": "section",
  "stylesheet": "fpq-banner.css",
  "javascript": "fpq-banner.js",
  "settings": []
}
{% endschema %}
